{{Infobox settlement |official_name =Agricultural Research Station |native_name =ايستگاه تحقيقات كشاورزئ مغان |settlement_type = village/research station |subdivision_type = [[List of countries|Country]] |subdivision_name = {{flag|Iran}} |subdivision_type1 =[[Provinces of Iran|Province]] |subdivision_name1 =[[Ardabil Province|Ardabil]] |subdivision_type2 =[[Counties of Iran|County]] |subdivision_name2 = [[Parsabad County|Parsabad]] |subdivision_type3 =[[Bakhsh]] |subdivision_name3 =[[Central District (Parsabad County)|Central]] |subdivision_type4 =[[Rural Districts of Iran|Rural District]] |subdivision_name4 =[[Qeshlaq-e Shomali Rural District|Qeshlaq-e Shomali]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_title = |established_date = |area_total_km2 = |area_footnotes = |population_as_of = 2006 |population_total =139 |population_density_km2 =auto |timezone = [[Iran Standard Time|IRST]] |utc_offset = +3:30 |timezone_DST = [[Iran Daylight Time|IRDT]] |utc_offset_DST = +4:30 |coordinates = |elevation_m = |area_code = |website = |footnotes = }} '''Agricultural Research Station''' ({{lang-fa|ايستگاه تحقيقات كشاورزئ مغان}} &ndash; ''Īstgāh Taḥqīqāt Keshāvarzy Maghān'') is a research station and village in [[Qeshlaq-e Shomali Rural District]], in the [[Central District (Parsabad County)|Central District]] of [[Parsabad County]], [[Ardabil Province]], [[Iran]]. At the 2006 census, its population was 139, in 41 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|24}}</ref>
