{{more footnotes|date=February 2013}}
'''Carlyle A. Luer''' (born August 23, 1922<ref name=immigration>{{cite web|last=Luer|first=Carlyle August|title=Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Immigration Cards, 1900-1965|url=https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.1.1/KCXM-373|publisher=familysearch|accessdate=28 November 2013}}</ref>) is a [[botanist]] specializing in the [[Orchidaceae]]. His specialty interest is the [[Pleurothallidinae]] (Genus ''[[Pleurothallis]]'') and allied species.<ref name=selbyana>{{cite journal|title=Carlyle A. Luer |journal=Selbyana|date=2009|volume=30|issue=1|jstor=41760346}}</ref>

Born to Carl & Vera Luer,<ref name=immigration/> he was raised in [[Alton, Illinois]] and later attended [[Washington University, St. Louis]] School of Medicine, graduating in 1946.<ref name=alumni>{{cite web|title=Carlyle A. Luer, MD 46|publisher=Washington University, St. Louis School of Medicine Outlook Magazine|url=http://medalumni.wustl.edu/alumni/adev.nsf/0d99c5bea3f3ffa28625707b00566fb8/8f079396560efef5862571a4006d5652?OpenDocument|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/66qz5f5HE?url=http://medalumni.wustl.edu/alumni/adev.nsf/0d99c5bea3f3ffa28625707b00566fb8/8f079396560efef5862571a4006d5652?OpenDocument|archivedate=2012-04-11|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> From there he went on to be a surgeon in [[Sarasota, Florida]] and upon retirement in 1975 took up the study and botanical illustration of Orchids.<ref name=alumni />

He aided in the foundation of the [[Marie Selby Botanical Gardens]] and was the first editor of their research journal ''Selbyana''.<ref name=selbyana /> He has also been named a senior curator at the [[Missouri Botanical Garden]] and has published numerous articles and two books related to Orchid taxonomy.<ref name=alumni />

