'''Elisabeth Boyko''' (24 September 1892 - 14 December 1985) was an Austrian-Israeli [[botanist]] noted for pioneering the use of [[salt water]] for [[irrigation]] of desert plants in Israel, alongside her husband [[Hugo Boyko]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Bauer |first1=Clayton C. |title=Desert Hope - Salt-Water Irrigation |journal=The Rotarian |date=April 1964 |pages=26-29 |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=2zMEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA26 |accessdate=5 October 2018 |publisher=Rotary International |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Glenn |first1=Edward P. |last2=Brown |first2=J. Jed |last3=O’Leary |first3=James W. |title=Irrigating Crops with Seawater |journal=Scientific American |date=1998 |volume=279 |issue=2 |pages=76–81 |url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/26070601 |accessdate=5 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Doerr |first1=Arthur H. |last2=Coling |first2=Jerome F. |last3=William S. Kerr |first3=III |title=Agricultural Evolution in Israel in the Two Decades since Independence |journal=Middle East Journal |date=1970 |volume=24 |issue=3 |pages=319–337 |url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/4324615}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Ventura |first1=Yvonne |last2=Eshel |first2=Amram |last3=Pasternak |first3=Dov |last4=Sagi |first4=Moshe |title=The development of halophyte-based agriculture: past and present |journal=Annals of Botany |date=February 2015 |volume=115 |issue=3 |pages=529–540 |doi=10.1093/aob/mcu173 |url= https://watermark.silverchair.com/mcu173.pdf?token=AQECAHi208BE49Ooan9kkhW_Ercy7Dm3ZL_9Cf3qfKAc485ysgAAAhUwggIRBgkqhkiG9w0BBwagggICMIIB_gIBADCCAfcGCSqGSIb3DQEHATAeBglghkgBZQMEAS4wEQQMOPTJI0-MNhr10GH7AgEQgIIByIQMtmLN3XmmnsEOr0sPwq-XuH1Ujma7NYNh6BM994N5fgO4Y_C8IZycQw4jgvbNZQ-qd7QiVl8s6O-Vc0giL519H2X-Vruzw6y4hHJd331EqMF9MbXBSGud-V5-7bHELveCseZbJ2bnoIYU4gpoiUyUNn5cvJUjTEYlAo35ES0R4vzof1X_QW1e_F1wx3NJuajm5OraiqaJtoLnCWdYk1u74e9rqyNO3D-GrhC0pp5y13s3dJhh5__FhYnERXTMzF7W2SFS8dLUW16_sSukoNwwqckheMo7sIyHJjaFryC81EB0tzVLb8Y3-Y2Q_vEzLhCyZs20XMhdYF-lIAbSyUFdWWN3x6coAuEmIL5b8rXXuXRZlX0ld0v7B9oq_zqlqwZpSq0QrHkESMM3qcYJt-TJHksz8FHxlHXNg7t5k0s-u3-ppe2gfCAWVVUY1CYvPUHmms9v5K-PW36REd3qxZ9bWkJCln1DtWATnDt3LVXLkHDc-PNXEYlWeaQeqRWQL3FTNQ80OSPTNVQeytZOuMhmq4ISiMKSpA-3g-atyw-RZl-PhsppeVgWtfMFY87gn_5zg1K3pKQDvIqCcwhfQjIjy3Eef97ptg |accessdate=5 October 2018}}</ref>  She received the William F. Petersen Award from the [[International Society of Biometeorology]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Tromp |first1=Solco Walle |last2=Weihe |first2=Wolf H. |journal=Biometeorology: Proceedings of the International Biometeorological Congress |date=1970 |volume=4 |pages=35-36 |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=MzJQAAAAYAAJ |publisher=Pergamon Press |title=Proceedings of the 2d- International Biometeorological Congress|language=en}}</ref>

