{{about|the Green Canyon area in the Gulf of Mexico|the tourist destination in [[Pangandaran Regency]], Indonesia|Cukang Taneuh}} {{Location map | United States | lat_deg = 28 | lat_dir = N | lon_deg = 92 | lon_dir = W }}
'''Green Canyon''' is an area in the [[Gulf of Mexico]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.geographic.org/geographic_names/name.php?uni=-238382&fid=6444&c=undersea_features |title=Green Canyon: Undersea Features (Full name, Geographic coordinates, map) |work=Geographical Names |author=Geographic.org |accessdate=2013-04-13}}</ref> that is rich in [[oil field]]s and under the control of the [[Bureau of Ocean Energy Management]]. Among other oil fields Green Canyon consist of [[Atlantis Oil Field|Atlantis]] (blocks 699, 700, 742, 743, and 744) operated by [[BP]], [[Marco Polo Field|Marco Polo]] (block 608) and [[K2 Field|K2]] (blocks 518 and 562) operated by [[Anadarko Petroleum]], [[Manatee Field|Manatee]] (block 155) operated by [[Royal Dutch Shell|Shell]], [[Shenzi Field|Shenzi]] (blocks 609, 610, 653, and 654) operated by [[BHP Billiton]], [[Droshky Field|Droshky]] (block 244) operated by [[Marathon Oil]], [[Tahiti Field|Tahiti]] (blocks 596, 597, 640 and 641) operated by [[Chevron Corporation]].<ref name=atlantis> {{cite web |url=http://www.subseaiq.com/data/Project.aspx?project_id=144 |title=Atlantis |work=SubseaIQ | publisher= Rigzone |accessdate=2012-01-02}} </ref><ref name=marcopolo> {{cite web | url= http://www.offshore-technology.com/projects/marcopolo/ | title = Marco Polo Field, United States of America | work = Offshore Technology | accessdate=2012-01-02}} </ref><ref name=k2> {{cite web | url= http://www.offshore-technology.com/projects/k2-field/ | title = K2 Field, United States of America | work = Offshore Technology | accessdate=2012-01-02}} </ref><ref name=manatee> {{cite web | url= http://www.offshore-technology.com/projects/manatee/ | title = Manatee Field, Gulf of Mexico, United States of America | work = Offshore Technology | accessdate=2012-01-02}} </ref><ref name=shenzi> {{cite web | url= http://www.offshore-technology.com/projects/shenzi/ | title = Shenzi Field, United States of America | work = Offshore Technology | accessdate=2012-01-02}} </ref><ref name=droshky> {{cite web | url= http://www.offshore-technology.com/projects/droshkyfieldgulfofme/ | title = Droshky Field, Gulf of Mexico, United States of America | work = Offshore Technology | accessdate=2012-01-02}} </ref><ref name=tahiti> {{cite web | url= http://www.offshore-technology.com/projects/tahiti-field/ | title = Tahiti, United States of America | work = Offshore Technology | accessdate=2012-01-02}} </ref> <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.geographic.org/deepwater_gulf_of_mexico/appendixa.html |title=Appendix A. Announced Deepwater Discoveries (Sorted by Project Name) |work=Deepwater Gulf of Mexico - America's Expanding Frontier |accessdate=2013-04-13}}</ref>
Green Canyon, block 185 is known as Bush Hill and is a well known [[cold seep]] with a wide array of [[Lamellibrachia luymesi|tube worms]]. In this area, the first time in Gulf of Mexico [[gas hydrates]] were recovered in piston cores.<ref name=buster> {{cite book | url= https://books.google.com/books?id=gHDQD9Q5Zb4C&pg=PA249 | title = Gulf of Mexico Origin, Waters, and Biota | volume = 3 | series = Harte Research Institute for Gulf of Mexico Studies Series | first1 = Noreen A. | last1 = Buster | first2 = Charles W. | last2 = Holmes | publisher = [[Texas A&M University Press]] | year = 2011 | page =249 | isbn = 978-1-60344-290-9 }}</ref> <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.geographic.org/deepwater_gulf_of_mexico/leasing_activity.html#figure8 |title=Leasing Activity: Figure 8. Gas hydrates on the seafloor in Green Canyon Block 185 |work=Deepwater Gulf of Mexico - America's Expanding Frontier |accessdate=2013-04-13}}</ref>
Additionally, like most of the Gulf of Mexico, there is a significant amount of [[salt tectonics]].
Blocks in this protraction area are defined in [[Universal Transverse Mercator coordinate system | UTM]] zone 15 north in feet.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gomr.boemre.gov/homepg/pubinfo/MapsandSpatialData.html |accessdate=2011-08-30 |title=Gulf of Mexico: Maps and Spatial Data |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110823081500/http://www.gomr.boemre.gov/homepg/pubinfo/MapsandSpatialData.html |archivedate=2011-08-23 |df= }}</ref>
{{Geographic location |Center = '''Green Canyon''' |North = [[Ewing Bank]] |Northeast = [[Mississippi Canyon]] |East = [[Atwater Valley]] |Southeast = [[Lund Canyon]] |South = [[Walker Ridge]] |Southwest = [[Keathley Canyon]] |West = [[Garden Banks]] |Northwest = [[South Marsh Island]] }}
