'''Helmut Gams''' (1893–1976) was a central European botanist. Born in [[Brno]], he moved to [[Zürich]] as a child. He studied at the [[University of Zurich]], being awarded a PhD in 1918. During his career, he worked at the [[Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich|University of Munich]] and the [[University of Innsbruck]]. His research saw him pursue [[fieldwork]] around Europe and Asia. He specialized in [[mosses]] and [[lichens]].<ref>{{cite journal|title=Nachruf auf em. o. Univ.-Prof. Dr. phil. Helmut Gams (1893-1976)|journal=Berichte des Naturwissenschaftlich Medizinischen Vereins in Innsbruck|language=German|author= Pitschmann H|year=1977|volume=64|pages=207-222|url=http://www.zobodat.at/pdf/BERI_64_0207-0222.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author=Franz H|year=1978|title=In memoriam Univ.-Prof. Dr. Helmut Gams|journal=Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Österreich|language=German|volume=116-7|pages=5-6|url=http://www.zobodat.at/pdf/VZBG_116-117_0005-0006.pdf}}</ref>
{{botanist|Gams}}
