{{other uses2|Japan Academy Prize}} {{Use dmy dates|date=March 2014}} The {{Nihongo|'''Imperial Prize of the Japan Academy'''|恩賜賞|onshishō}} is a prestigious honor conferred to two of the recipients of the [[Japan Academy Prize (academics)|Japan Academy Prize]]. It is awarded in two categories: humanities and natural sciences<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.japan-acad.go.jp/en/activities/|title=The Imperial Prize, Japan Academy Prize, Duke of Edinburgh Prize|author=|date=|publisher=[[Japan Academy|Imperial Academy]]|accessdate=2017-06-27|lang=|quote=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160323135937/http://www.japan-acad.go.jp/en/activities/|archivedate=2016-03-23|ref=}}</ref>. The [[Emperor of Japan|Emperor]] and [[Empress of Japan|Empress]] visit the awarding ceremony and present a vase to the awardees.
