| alma_mater = University of Pune | thesis_title = <!--(or | thesis1_title = and | thesis2_title = )--> | thesis_url = <!--(or | thesis1_url = and | thesis2_url = )--> | thesis_year = <!--(or | thesis1_year = and | thesis2_year = )--> | doctoral_advisor = | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}--> | footnotes = }} '''Joyanti Chutia''' is an Indian physicist. She was the among the first women who have headed scientific institutions in India when she became the Director of the Institute of Advanced Study in Science and Technology in [[Guwahati]], [[Assam]] the first major research institution in North East India.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/sci-tech/indian-scientists-unearth-assams-muga-silks-wound-healing-powers_1519193.html | title=Indian scientists unearth Assam's Muga silk's wound-healing powers | publisher=[[Zee News]] | date=23 December 2014 | accessdate=26 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://gulfnews.com/news/asia/india/indian-scientists-unearth-wound-healing-powers-of-assam-s-muga-silk-1.1430826 | title=Indian scientists unearth wound-healing powers of Assam’s Muga silk | publisher=[[Gulf News]]| date=23 December 2014 | accessdate=26 April 2015}}</ref> She is a fellow of [[National Academy of Sciences, India|National Academy of Sciences]]. She is an Emeritus Scientist at the [[Department of Science and Technology (India)|Department of Science & Technology]] in the Government of India <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.harmonyindia.org/hportal/VirtualPageView.jsp?page_id=16607 | title=Science weds art | publisher=Harmony India | accessdate=26 April 2015 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304091633/http://www.harmonyindia.org/hportal/VirtualPageView.jsp?page_id=16607 | archivedate=4 March 2016 | df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nasi.org.in/ZONE%20-2015.pdf | title=Zone wise list of Fellows & Honorary Fellows (2015 ) | publisher=National Academy of Sciences | accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sentinelassam.com/state1/story.php?sec=2&subsec=2&id=204625&dtP=2014-09-30&ppr=1 | title=Women scientists continue to face discrimination’ | publisher=The Sentinel | accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.freepressjournal.in/indian-scientists-unearth-muga-silks-wound-healing-powers/ | title=Indian scientists unearth Muga silks wound-healing powers | newspaper=[[Free Press Journal]] | date=21 October 2014 | accessdate=18 November 2015 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151119183609/http://www.freepressjournal.in/indian-scientists-unearth-muga-silks-wound-healing-powers/ | archivedate=19 November 2015 | df= }}</ref>
== Early life and education == Joyanti became involved in physics when she was a student in the [[Cotton College, Guwahati|Cotton College]] in Assam. After finishing her fellowship given by the Japanese Government in 1988 to work in the Plasma Laboratory of the [[Institute of Space and Astronautical Science]], Tokyo, in 2005 she became the Director of the Institute of Advanced Study in Science and Technology.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ias.ac.in/womeninscience/LD_essays/91-93.pdf | title=My experience with research | publisher=www.ias.ac.in | accessdate=26 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ewwomen.in/jchutia/ | title=Prof. Joyanti Chutia | publisher=www.ewwomen.in | accessdate=18 November 2015 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151119060112/http://www.ewwomen.in/jchutia/ | archivedate=19 November 2015 | df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title = INDIA-AUSTRALIA WORKSHOP ON BIOTECHNOLOGY ORGANISED| work =Report from the [[Assam Tribune]] brought to you by HT Syndication [[Hindustan Times]]| date = 22 October 2008| accessdate = 18 November 2015| url = https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1581293231.html | publisher = via HighBeam {{Subscription required}} }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=KAMAL KUMARI NATIONAL AWARDS PRESENTED|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1014170351.html|newspaper=[[Hindustan Times]] {{Subscription required|via=HighBeam}}|accessdate=18 November 2015|date=2 April 2006}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|title=IASST CELEBRATES FOUNDATION DAY|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1158910171.html|publisher=Report from the [[Assam Tribune]] brought to you by HT Syndication [[Hindustan Times]]{{Subscription required|via=HighBeam}}|accessdate=18 November 2015|date=8 November 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=WORKSHOP ON PLANT DIVERSITY HELD|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1600605301.html|publisher=Report from the [[Assam Tribune]] brought to you by HT Syndication [[Hindustan Times]]{{Subscription required|vi